      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "off - No limits are applied to the pixel values. clamp - Pixel values are constrained to the ranged defined by the Minimum and Maximum parameters. Values outside of the range are replaced with the Minimum or Maximum value. loop - Values outside of the Minimum/Maximum range continue at the other end of the interval e.g. as values go above the Maximum they loop back and start again at the Minimum value. zigzag - When values go beyond the Minimum or Maximum values they mirror back towards the other end of the range e.g. when a value goes above the maximum it flips and starts going back to the minimum.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
